WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:24.840
Princess Diana by Anne Collins, published by Macmillan Education, a division of Macmillan

00:24.840 --> 00:29.480
Publishers Limited, 2009.

00:42.600 --> 00:53.720
Introduction Princess Diana was a very famous British woman. In August 1997 Diana was

00:53.720 --> 01:00.880
on holiday in the Mediterranean with her new man Dodie Al-Fayed. There were holiday

01:00.880 --> 01:08.640
photographs of them in the newspapers. Diana looked happy. Then just a few days

01:08.640 --> 01:16.520
later she was dead. She died suddenly on the 31st of August in a car accident in

01:16.600 --> 01:25.040
Paris. There are many books about Diana's life. We often see her photograph and hear

01:25.040 --> 01:32.880
her name. She was beautiful and famous. She was a modern princess and a loving mother.

01:32.880 --> 01:41.800
She wanted to help people. But her life was not always happy. This is Diana's story.

01:46.520 --> 01:57.640
Chapter 1 The Early Years

01:57.640 --> 02:07.160
Diana's parents were Francis and Johnny Spencer, the Viscount Althorp. Johnny was from a very

02:07.160 --> 02:15.560
old and important English family, the Spencer family. George Washington, Humphrey Bogart,

02:15.560 --> 02:23.200
and Rudolf Valentino were connected to this family. Francis was beautiful but she was

02:23.200 --> 02:30.800
also a very strong woman. She fell in love with Johnny Althorp when she was only 17 years

02:30.800 --> 02:39.760
old. Johnny Althorp was tall and handsome and Francis wanted to marry him. Johnny went

02:39.760 --> 02:47.280
to Eton, one of the most famous private schools in England. And then he was an officer in

02:47.280 --> 02:55.880
the army. Later he left the army and studied farming. Francis and Johnny married on the

02:55.880 --> 03:04.440
1st of June 1954 at St. Margaret's Church, Westminster, in London. A thousand people

03:04.440 --> 03:10.400
were at the wedding. The Queen, the Duke of Edinburgh, the Queen Mother, and the Queen's

03:10.400 --> 03:19.880
sister, Princess Margaret, all came. Francis and Johnny lived at Park House in Norfolk.

03:19.880 --> 03:27.000
The royal family had a house nearby called Sandringham House. The royals often came to

03:27.000 --> 03:36.880
Sandringham on holiday. They knew the Spencer family well. When Francis' father died, he

03:36.880 --> 03:44.320
left her a lot of money. Francis used the money to buy a farm at Snettisham near Park House.

03:44.320 --> 03:57.960
In 1955, the couple had a daughter, Sarah, and in 1957, another daughter, Jane. In 1960,

03:57.960 --> 04:06.280
they had another child. This time it was a boy called John, but he died after only 10 hours.

04:07.200 --> 04:19.200
Then, on the 1st of July 1961, Diana was born. And three years later, in May 1964, Francis and

04:19.200 --> 04:30.000
Johnny had a boy, Charles. But there were problems in the marriage. In 1966, Francis met a new man,

04:30.480 --> 04:41.920
Peter Shand Kidd, at a party in London. Francis and Peter fell in love. At Christmas, 1967,

04:41.920 --> 04:51.040
Francis left Johnny and moved to London. She wanted to take the children with her. Johnny wanted

04:51.040 --> 05:00.000
them to stay at Park House with him. Diana missed her mother very much. She was only six years

05:00.000 --> 05:07.840
old when Francis left. Her sisters were at boarding school, a type of school where they lived most

05:07.840 --> 05:18.000
of the time. It was a sad and very difficult time for Diana and Charles. After Francis left,

05:18.640 --> 05:24.640
Johnny paid money to different women, called nannies, to look after the children at Park House.

05:26.240 --> 05:34.720
The Spencer children loved Park House. It was a large and friendly house. Diana loved animals

05:34.720 --> 05:43.200
like dogs, cats, and rabbits. She enjoyed swimming, playing tennis, and going for picnics on the beach.

05:44.000 --> 05:53.120
She visited her mother in London at the weekends. Sometimes the royal family invited the Spencer

05:53.120 --> 05:59.920
children to the big house at Sandringham. Diana was good friends with Prince Charles's younger

05:59.920 --> 06:10.720
brother, Prince Andrew. Diana's mother and father divorced in April 1969. Francis married Peter

06:10.720 --> 06:18.000
Shand Kidd soon after. Diana and her brother had holidays with Peter and his three children.

06:19.840 --> 06:28.480
Later, Francis and Peter bought a big house on the Isle of Seil. Seil was an island near the west

06:28.480 --> 06:36.960
coast of Scotland. Diana went to a small day school near her home, called Silfield.

06:37.760 --> 06:44.960
But when she was nine, her father sent her to boarding school. The school was called Riddlesworth

06:44.960 --> 06:55.600
Hall. In September 1973, when Diana was 12, she moved to another school called West Heath.

06:57.120 --> 07:05.520
West Heath was near the town of Seven Oaks in Kent. Diana liked her new school. She had some good

07:05.520 --> 07:13.120
friends there. She learned to dance and play the piano. She was not very interested in school

07:13.120 --> 07:22.000
exams, but she was good at dancing and swimming. At this time, Johnny Althorpe met a new woman.

07:23.120 --> 07:31.760
Her name was Rain Leg, the Countess of Dartmouth. Rain was also the writer Barbara Cartland's daughter.

07:31.840 --> 07:39.760
Rain was married with four children. Johnny's children loved their father very much,

07:39.760 --> 07:47.680
and they did not want him to be with another woman. Then, on the 9th of June 1975,

07:47.680 --> 07:57.040
Johnny's father Jack died. Jack was the seventh Earl Spencer. Now Johnny became the eighth Earl

07:57.120 --> 08:06.400
Spencer, and Diana became Lady Diana Spencer. Johnny and his family went to live in his father's

08:06.400 --> 08:13.920
great house at Althorpe in Northampton. The Spencer children did not like Althorpe very much.

08:15.120 --> 08:24.240
It was a very big house in a large park. It had 121 rooms. It was a beautiful house,

08:25.120 --> 08:30.080
but it was also very cold. It was not a home-like park house.

08:32.080 --> 08:40.400
Rain started to come to Althorpe a lot. In May 1976, Rain and her husband divorced.

08:41.760 --> 08:47.040
Two months later in July, Johnny and Rain married quietly in London.

08:47.040 --> 08:54.320
Johnny did not tell his children about the wedding. They read about it in the newspapers.

08:56.320 --> 09:03.280
The Spencer children were very angry with their father. Now Rain lived at Althorpe all the time.

09:04.640 --> 09:11.760
Diana loved her father, but he was now married to Rain. This was very difficult for Diana.

09:12.320 --> 09:19.200
Many of Rain and Johnny's friends visited Althorpe. They had a lot of parties there.

09:20.400 --> 09:23.200
But the Spencer girls were always cold to Rain.

09:25.280 --> 09:34.800
In 1978, Johnny was very ill and was close to death. Rain looked after him and helped save his life.

09:35.680 --> 09:42.000
Johnny was lucky, and he got better. But still the children did not like Rain.

09:54.640 --> 09:57.600
Chapter 2 The Prince

09:57.920 --> 10:05.440
Prince Charles was born on the 14th of November 1948 at Buckingham Palace.

10:06.960 --> 10:12.480
He is the oldest of the Queen's four children. He is also the Prince of Wales.

10:14.560 --> 10:21.920
After the King or Queen dies, the Prince of Wales usually becomes King. So Charles is heir to the

10:21.920 --> 10:28.960
throne or the next King. When he was a boy, Charles was very shy.

10:30.480 --> 10:36.320
He went first to a day school in London. Later, his parents sent him to Gordonston,

10:37.040 --> 10:43.840
a boarding school in North East Scotland. Life for Charles at Gordonston was very hard.

10:44.960 --> 10:51.840
Charles was sad there and did not have any friends. He did not see his parents very often.

10:52.480 --> 11:00.160
Later, Charles went to Cambridge University. Then he was an officer in the Royal Navy,

11:00.960 --> 11:09.200
the part of the armed forces that works at sea. He was in the Navy for five years. He was a pilot

11:09.200 --> 11:16.400
and flew planes and helicopters. Charles enjoyed horse riding and loved playing polo,

11:17.120 --> 11:22.800
a game for people riding on horses. He also liked hunting and shooting animals,

11:23.360 --> 11:31.840
for example birds and deer with a gun. When Charles was 23, in the summer of 1970,

11:32.400 --> 11:41.440
he met Camilla Shand at a polo match. Camilla was 15 months older than Charles. Camilla was pretty

11:41.440 --> 11:48.400
and fun. She liked the same things as Charles. She loved horses, dogs,

11:48.400 --> 11:55.280
the countryside and hunting. Charles and Camilla spent weekends together at the home of Earl Mount

11:55.280 --> 12:02.960
Baton. Earl Mount Baton was Charles's father's uncle. Charles was very close to Earl Mount

12:03.040 --> 12:10.720
Baton. He called the Earl Grandpa. But Camilla married another young man called Andrew Parker

12:10.720 --> 12:21.360
Bowles in July 1973. After that, Charles had many girlfriends. The newspapers started calling him

12:21.360 --> 12:30.320
the Playboy Prince. Charles liked tall, blonde women. Some of his girlfriends were Divina Sheffield,

12:30.880 --> 12:39.760
Anna Wallace and Mount Baton's granddaughter, Amanda Nachpal. Charles also had friends who

12:39.760 --> 12:47.360
were married women. One of these was an Australian woman called Dale Trion. Her friends called her

12:47.360 --> 12:55.200
kanga, like the Australian animal kangaroo. But the most important woman friend for Charles

12:55.200 --> 13:02.560
was still Camilla Parker Bowles. Camilla and Andrew Parker Bowles were now married with two

13:02.560 --> 13:08.480
children. Andrew Parker Bowles knew about his wife's friendship with Prince Charles,

13:09.280 --> 13:15.280
but he was not unhappy about it. In fact, Andrew and Prince Charles were friends.

13:15.280 --> 13:25.360
Then something exciting happened. Sarah Spencer, Diana's older sister, met Prince Charles at a

13:25.360 --> 13:32.560
party at Windsor Castle in the summer of 1977. She went to watch the Prince playing polo.

13:34.000 --> 13:40.880
Later they went on a skiing holiday together. The queen invited Sarah to Balmoral, the royal

13:40.880 --> 13:48.400
family's Scottish home. That November, Sarah invited Prince Charles to all thought for the weekend.

13:49.440 --> 13:56.000
Diana was there too. She first met Prince Charles in the countryside near her home.

13:57.040 --> 14:05.760
She was just 16 years old. In April 1978, Diana's sister Jane got married.

14:06.560 --> 14:15.520
Her husband was Robert Fellows, the son of a Norfolk family. Later Robert Fellows had a very

14:15.520 --> 14:24.000
important job. He was private secretary to the queen, helping her and working very closely with her.

14:26.000 --> 14:34.400
Sarah's romance with Prince Charles ended. On the 14th of November 1978, the prince had a dance

14:34.480 --> 14:42.160
for his 30th birthday at Buckingham Palace. He invited Sarah, but he invited Diana too.

14:43.520 --> 14:49.200
Diana was very surprised and excited. She liked Prince Charles very much.

14:51.360 --> 14:58.000
Mountbatten wanted Charles to marry and have children. Charles usually listened to Mountbatten,

14:58.800 --> 15:06.240
but he did not want to get married. He did not need a wife. He liked painting pictures

15:06.240 --> 15:14.800
and he liked reading books. He had his girlfriends. He also had servants or people who worked for him

15:14.800 --> 15:25.840
to do things for him. Then in 1979, the IRA, Irish Republican army, killed Earl Mountbatten

15:25.920 --> 15:34.400
with a bomb in his fishing boat. Mountbatten was dead and Charles was shocked and very sad.

15:34.400 --> 15:47.280
I have lost someone very special in my life, he said.

15:52.320 --> 16:00.720
Chapter 3 The fairy story begins. Diana was now a young woman of 17.

16:01.600 --> 16:09.840
She wanted to go and live in London. Both her sisters Sarah and Jane lived there. They worked

16:09.840 --> 16:18.160
for Vogue magazine. But Diana was not interested in a job that paid lots of money. She loved

16:18.160 --> 16:25.760
children and was very good with them. So she went to London and found jobs looking after children.

16:26.640 --> 16:35.440
Diana was very happy with her new life. Her mother, Francis, had a flat in Cadogan Square,

16:36.400 --> 16:43.120
a very wealthy part of London. Diana lived in the flat with two girlfriends.

16:44.800 --> 16:51.200
In July 1979, her mother bought her a flat in London for her 18th birthday.

16:52.000 --> 17:00.480
The address was 60 Colhern Court, Chelsea. Diana lived there with three friends.

17:01.840 --> 17:09.520
Caroline Pride, or Caroline Bartholomew after she was married. Anne Bolton and Virginia Pitman.

17:11.040 --> 17:18.800
Diana enjoyed London. She did not like parties, but sometimes she went to dances at country houses.

17:19.760 --> 17:24.080
But she liked sitting at home and watching television with her girlfriends.

17:26.400 --> 17:33.360
In May 1980, Diana's sister Sarah married Neil McCorkardale, an officer in the army.

17:34.800 --> 17:41.440
The married couple lived in Chelsea too, near Diana. Diana often went to Sarah's house.

17:42.400 --> 17:45.840
Sometimes Sarah paid Diana to clean her house for her.

17:45.840 --> 17:55.280
Diana was now 19 years old. She was a happy, pretty young woman. Life was good for her.

17:57.040 --> 18:03.200
Diana met Charles again in July 1980, at a house party in West Sussex.

18:04.640 --> 18:10.640
He invited her to go with him on the Royal Yacht, a large boat called Britannia.

18:10.640 --> 18:17.280
They were on the boat at cows in the Isle of Wight, an island off the south of England.

18:18.960 --> 18:24.800
Later, in September, Prince Charles invited Diana to stay at Balmoral in Scotland.

18:26.320 --> 18:34.240
He invited some other friends too, but they were all much older than Diana. Diana's sister Jane

18:34.240 --> 18:40.240
and her husband Robert Fellows were there. Camilla and Andrew Parker Bowles were there too.

18:41.040 --> 18:45.200
Charles started seeing Diana more and more.

18:46.720 --> 18:50.400
The newspapers were very interested in Charles' romantic life.

18:51.440 --> 18:54.880
Soon they knew all about his beautiful new girlfriend.

18:56.560 --> 18:59.040
One story in the Sun newspaper said,

18:59.840 --> 19:04.400
He's in love again. Lady Di is the new girl for Charles.

19:04.400 --> 19:11.120
The newspaper reporters, the people who write the stories for newspapers,

19:12.160 --> 19:18.480
came to Diana's flat at 60 Col Hearn Court in London. They waited outside.

19:19.440 --> 19:26.080
All the reporters wanted to take photographs of her. Diana was always nice to the reporters.

19:27.040 --> 19:30.080
The reporters liked her and became her friends.

19:30.080 --> 19:34.960
The newspapers started calling her, Shy Die.

19:37.440 --> 19:42.480
On the 14th of November 1980, Charles was 32 years old.

19:43.840 --> 19:47.520
The newspapers and Charles' family asked the same question.

19:48.720 --> 19:51.760
Is Prince Charles going to marry Lady Diana?

19:53.520 --> 19:59.520
In January 1981, Charles went on a skiing holiday to clusters in Switzerland.

20:00.720 --> 20:03.120
When he was there, he telephoned Diana.

20:04.320 --> 20:06.640
I've got something to ask you, he said.

20:08.080 --> 20:15.200
Diana was very excited. She sat with her girlfriend's very late at night, talking about Prince Charles.

20:17.120 --> 20:21.360
When Charles returned from his holiday, he asked Diana to marry him.

20:22.480 --> 20:23.760
Diana said yes.

20:24.720 --> 20:32.240
On the 24th of February 1981, Buckingham Palace told the country that Charles, Prince of Wales,

20:32.240 --> 20:35.120
was going to marry Lady Diana Spencer.

20:36.160 --> 20:40.880
Charles and Diana gave a television interview in the Garden of Buckingham Palace.

20:42.400 --> 20:45.760
Can you find the right words to say how you feel today?

20:46.560 --> 20:47.760
Asked the interviewer.

20:47.760 --> 20:55.120
Difficult to find the right sort of words, said Charles, just delighted and happy.

20:56.080 --> 20:59.520
And I suppose in love, asked the interviewer.

21:00.240 --> 21:02.800
Of course, said Diana Shiley.

21:03.920 --> 21:07.360
Whatever in love means, Charles answered.

21:09.280 --> 21:13.120
Two nights later, Diana went to live at Buckingham Palace.

21:13.760 --> 21:17.760
Most people in Britain were very happy about Charles and Diana.

21:19.040 --> 21:24.560
People liked reading about Charles' girlfriends, but now it was time for him to marry.

21:25.520 --> 21:28.320
Everyone was excited about the royal wedding.

21:29.840 --> 21:33.760
Many people thought that Diana was the perfect wife for Charles.

21:34.720 --> 21:38.320
She was a beautiful young girl, tall and blonde.

21:38.480 --> 21:45.200
She was very sweet and shy, and, very importantly for the royal family,

21:45.840 --> 21:48.160
Prince Charles was her first boyfriend.

21:49.360 --> 21:54.560
Because of this, the newspapers could not write stories about Diana and other boyfriends.

21:55.680 --> 21:58.160
Camilla was also happy about Diana.

21:58.960 --> 22:02.640
Camilla was married and had a husband, Andrew Parker Bowles.

22:03.280 --> 22:04.960
She could not be Charles' wife.

22:05.600 --> 22:08.240
But Charles was going to be the next king.

22:08.880 --> 22:12.320
He needed to have children, so he had to marry someone.

22:12.960 --> 22:15.120
And Diana was a very sweet girl.

22:17.360 --> 22:22.160
Diana found her new life at Buckingham Palace, lonely and a little difficult.

22:23.200 --> 22:26.480
She had to meet lots of new people and learn new things.

22:28.080 --> 22:30.640
Charles invited Diana to his friend's homes.

22:31.520 --> 22:33.520
Often Camilla was there too.

22:34.880 --> 22:37.680
Camilla often talked to Diana about Charles.

22:38.960 --> 22:40.800
Diana was very surprised.

22:41.760 --> 22:43.680
Why was Camilla all was there?

22:44.240 --> 22:46.800
And how did she know so much about Charles?

22:48.640 --> 22:52.880
Charles and Diana were married on the 29th of July, 1981.

22:53.600 --> 22:55.440
It was a beautiful summer's day.

22:56.080 --> 22:58.240
It was a perfect romantic wedding.

22:59.040 --> 23:05.600
750 million people in more than 70 countries watched the wedding on television.

23:06.880 --> 23:09.280
Lady Di was now Princess Di.

23:10.240 --> 23:12.240
She was not a shy young girl now.

23:12.800 --> 23:13.840
She was a princess.

23:15.600 --> 23:17.520
Diana looked beautiful at her wedding.

23:18.320 --> 23:21.520
She was in love with her husband and she was very happy.

23:22.560 --> 23:25.760
She wore a wonderful, long dress of expensive silk.

23:25.760 --> 23:32.000
Later, after the wedding, the new couple kissed outside Buckingham Palace.

23:33.200 --> 23:38.240
People all around the world watched the kiss and were happy for Charles and Diana.

23:39.280 --> 23:42.160
And thousands of people waited in the streets of London.

23:42.880 --> 23:44.640
They wanted to see the royal couple.

23:46.800 --> 23:50.320
After the wedding, Charles and Diana went to Broadlands,

23:50.960 --> 23:53.680
Mountbatten's country home, for two days.

23:54.400 --> 23:59.920
Then they went on honeymoon, the holiday after a wedding, on the Royal Yacht Britannia.

24:01.520 --> 24:03.760
But it was not a very private honeymoon.

24:04.400 --> 24:07.040
There were 200 sailors working on the ship too.

24:07.760 --> 24:10.320
So Charles and Diana were not alone very much.

24:11.920 --> 24:17.840
Charles liked reading books written by his friend, the South African writer, Laurent Vanderpost.

24:18.720 --> 24:22.000
He brought some of Vanderpost's books with him on the honeymoon.

24:22.800 --> 24:24.320
He sat on the boat reading them.

24:25.680 --> 24:30.560
Diana was not interested in these books, so she talked to the sailors and cooks.

24:32.720 --> 24:38.960
Later, in September of that year, Charles and Diana went on holiday to Balmoral in Scotland.

24:40.400 --> 24:44.080
The Queen, the Duke of Edinburgh and the Queen Mother were there too.

24:45.520 --> 24:51.120
Diana liked Scotland, but she did not like the same things as Charles and other people in his family.

24:52.080 --> 24:54.320
She did not like hunting and shooting animals.

24:55.440 --> 24:57.600
Diana did not feel part of the family.

24:59.440 --> 25:03.920
In October, Charles and Diana went to Wales for their first public visit.

25:05.520 --> 25:10.320
Newspaper and television reporters came from all over the world to take pictures of Diana.

25:11.200 --> 25:14.000
They were very interested in the new Princess of Wales.

25:15.760 --> 25:19.920
Diana did not feel well. She was pregnant with her first baby.

25:20.560 --> 25:24.560
But she got out of the car and walked in the streets to meet people.

25:25.440 --> 25:27.120
She knew how to talk to people.

25:28.080 --> 25:30.320
She talked to children and old people.

25:31.120 --> 25:33.360
And she talked in public for the first time.

25:34.240 --> 25:38.160
She made this speech in Welsh, the national language of Wales.

25:39.360 --> 25:40.800
Everyone loved Diana.

25:41.520 --> 25:45.600
They shouted, we want die, we want die, we want die.

25:45.600 --> 25:51.120
The people were more interested in Diana than in her husband, Prince Charles.

25:53.280 --> 25:59.920
On the 21st of June 1982, Diana and Charles's first son, Prince William was born.

26:01.280 --> 26:04.080
Prince Charles was with Diana at the hospital all day.

26:05.440 --> 26:08.240
When William was born, Charles was very happy.

26:09.840 --> 26:12.480
It was only 11 months after the royal wedding.

26:13.360 --> 26:17.360
Diana was not a young, shy girl living in a flat with friends now.

26:18.080 --> 26:22.000
She was a royal wife and she was mother of the future king.

26:23.040 --> 26:25.120
It was a big change in Diana's life.

26:26.640 --> 26:29.520
Everybody was very excited about the baby prince.

26:30.640 --> 26:36.160
Diana and Charles arrived home from the hospital and the crowds of people waved and shouted.

26:36.880 --> 26:38.880
It was a happy time for the princess.

26:42.800 --> 26:46.480
The New Year

26:51.680 --> 26:52.640
Chapter 4

26:53.600 --> 26:54.720
We Want Die

26:56.480 --> 26:58.880
Charles and Diana had a new London home.

26:59.840 --> 27:03.600
This home was an apartment or flat in Kensington Palace.

27:04.880 --> 27:08.960
Some other members of the royal family had apartments in Kensington Palace, too.

27:08.960 --> 27:16.240
The Queen's sister, Princess Margaret, lived there. Princess Margaret had a party for Charles

27:16.240 --> 27:22.200
and Diana and the baby. Charles also had a house in Gloucestershire,

27:22.200 --> 27:28.880
in the west of England. This house was called High Grove. It was near the home of Camilla

27:28.880 --> 27:34.000
and Andrew Parker Bowles. Charles and Camilla often went hunting together

27:34.000 --> 27:42.560
in the countryside near High Grove. After Prince William was born, Diana became ill.

27:42.560 --> 27:49.680
She began to have problems with eating. She had an illness called bulimia nervosa. She

27:49.680 --> 27:57.560
often ate a lot of food, then made herself sick. Charles was worried about his wife,

27:57.560 --> 28:04.760
and he did not understand her problems. Diana started to look unwell. She became very

28:04.760 --> 28:12.200
thin. Some newspaper reporters began to ask questions about her health. Diana read these

28:12.200 --> 28:20.640
stories in the newspapers, and she became very unhappy. In March 1983, Charles and Diana

28:20.640 --> 28:27.680
went to visit different places in Australia. They took the baby, Prince William, with them.

28:27.680 --> 28:35.080
This tour of Australia was very successful. It was the beginning of Diamania. Everybody

28:35.080 --> 28:42.520
was crazy about Diana. Everybody loved her and wanted to see her. Hundreds of photographers

28:42.600 --> 28:49.400
came from countries all over the world. They all wanted photos of Diana for their newspapers.

28:49.400 --> 28:57.200
Charles and Diana visited many of Australia's cities. Almost one million people came to

28:57.200 --> 29:03.960
see them. In each city, Charles and Diana did a walkabout. They walked in the crowded

29:03.960 --> 29:11.360
city streets and talked to the people. But the people wanted to see Diana more than Charles.

29:11.360 --> 29:20.520
We want die, they shouted. Later that year, Charles and Diana went on a tour of Canada.

29:20.520 --> 29:29.320
This tour was also a big success. But again, the people's favourite was Diana, not Charles.

29:29.320 --> 29:36.240
This was very difficult for Charles. Diana was very good at talking to people. She talked

29:36.240 --> 29:43.160
to people of all ages, old and young. She talked to sick people too. When she smiled

29:43.160 --> 29:48.740
at people, they felt happy. A newspaper in America wrote,

29:48.740 --> 29:56.040
Diamania is the most popular woman in the world. The French magazine, Paris Match, wrote,

29:56.040 --> 30:03.440
Diana is more popular than the actress Bridget Bardot. Charles and Diana went on holiday

30:03.440 --> 30:11.320
in April 1983 to the Bahamas. The photographers took pictures of them on a beach. Charles

30:11.320 --> 30:18.240
and Diana walked hand in hand. They looked happy and in love.

30:18.240 --> 30:25.720
Diana became pregnant again. On the 15th of September 1984, the baby was born. It was

30:25.720 --> 30:33.080
another boy. His name was Prince Henry Charles Albert David. Everyone called him Prince

30:33.080 --> 30:41.280
Harry. Now William had a brother. Soon after Harry was born, Diana started to work for

30:41.280 --> 30:49.560
charities, groups which help people in need. She became president of Bernardo's, the Children's

30:49.560 --> 30:56.720
Charity. She visited Bernardo's children's homes all over the UK, United Kingdom and

30:56.720 --> 31:04.640
talk to people there. Some people in Bernardo's had very sad lives. They felt better when they

31:04.640 --> 31:12.120
talked to Diana about their problems. And Diana was good at listening to their stories.

31:12.120 --> 31:18.640
The newspapers loved writing about Diana's clothes and hair. When the Queen opened Parliament

31:18.640 --> 31:24.600
one year, the newspapers were not very interested. Diana's clothes were more important.

31:24.600 --> 31:34.880
In 1985, Charles and Diana went on tours to Italy, Australia and the USA, the United States of America.

31:34.880 --> 31:43.520
In America, Charles and Diana visited President Reagan and his wife Nancy. President Reagan gave

31:43.520 --> 31:50.640
a big dance for the couple. Diana wore a beautiful black dress and danced with the famous actor

31:50.640 --> 32:00.080
John Travolta. She looked very happy. Diana was no longer shy die. She was beautiful and she could

32:00.080 --> 32:07.920
dress well. She had a wonderful smile. But she also cared about people. She talked to them and made

32:07.920 --> 32:16.320
them happy. Everyone loved her. But at this time, some reporters started writing about problems in

32:16.320 --> 32:22.480
Charles and Diana's marriage. They said that there were big differences between Charles and Diana.

32:22.480 --> 32:30.960
Diana is a very young 24. Charles is a very old 36. wrote one newspaper.

32:30.960 --> 32:53.240
Chapter 5 The problems begin. Diana was the wife of Prince Charles and the mother of Prince's

32:53.240 --> 33:00.520
William and Harry. She was a very important person. So a policeman had to go everywhere with her.

33:00.520 --> 33:08.280
This policeman's job was to protect Diana and look after her. When Diana walked in the park,

33:08.280 --> 33:14.920
the policeman went with her. When she went shopping or out in the evenings, he went to.

33:15.800 --> 33:24.040
The princess became very close to one policeman, Barry Manikey. When she took William and Harry out,

33:24.040 --> 33:31.400
Manikey went to. The newspapers showed many photographs of Diana with her sons and Barry Manikey.

33:31.400 --> 33:39.080
Some people began to think, Princess Diana is in love with Barry Manikey. This was not good for

33:39.560 --> 33:45.720
Prince Charles or the royal family. So Manikey lost his job of looking after the princess.

33:47.080 --> 33:54.680
Two years later, Manikey died in a motorbike accident. Another new person came into Diana's

33:54.680 --> 34:04.040
life. This was Sarah Ferguson, usually called Fergie. Sarah was older than Diana. Her father,

34:04.040 --> 34:10.040
Ronald Ferguson, was Prince Charles's polo manager, the person who trains the polo team.

34:11.560 --> 34:18.440
Sarah and Diana first met at a polo match. Sarah lived in a flat in London with friends.

34:19.400 --> 34:27.000
She had lots of red hair and loved having fun. Sarah and Diana started having lunch together

34:27.080 --> 34:35.240
every week. Diana invited Fergie to dinner at Kensington Palace. There she met Prince

34:35.240 --> 34:43.720
Charles' younger brother, Prince Andrew. Fergie and Andrew fell in love. They married on the 23rd

34:43.720 --> 34:53.080
of July, 1986, in another big royal wedding. Diana and Fergie were friends, but Fergie was

34:53.080 --> 35:01.480
very different from Diana. She loved outdoor life and sports. She was very good at riding

35:01.480 --> 35:08.440
and she loved horses. She enjoyed going to Balmoral and doing things outdoors with the royal family.

35:10.200 --> 35:15.560
Charles and Diana were very different kinds of people. Charles was not interested in the

35:15.560 --> 35:22.040
same things as Diana. He could not understand her. He could not understand her problems with

35:22.040 --> 35:28.840
bulimia or that she needed help. Charles started seeing many of his old friends again.

35:29.800 --> 35:37.160
He spent a lot of time with Camilla Parker Bowles. Camilla understood Charles and made him feel good.

35:37.960 --> 35:44.600
She was not difficult like Diana. Diana knew that Charles was spending time with Camilla.

35:45.560 --> 35:51.160
She became angry and jealous. She felt that her husband did not love her anymore.

35:52.280 --> 35:57.720
So she started to see a young army officer. His name was James Hewitt.

35:59.560 --> 36:06.840
Diana and Hewitt met at a polo game. Hewitt was very good looking. He was kind

36:06.840 --> 36:14.600
and could talk to women easily. He was good at listening too. Later they met again at Buckingham

36:14.600 --> 36:19.320
Palace. Diana asked Hewitt to give her horse riding lessons.

36:20.040 --> 36:29.400
Hewitt cared about Diana and made her feel good. Diana told Hewitt about her bulimia and he listened.

36:30.760 --> 36:36.760
They spent weekends together at Hygrove. Sometimes they went to Hewitt's mother's house in Devon

36:36.760 --> 36:43.320
in the south west of England. Sometimes Charles liked going to places by himself.

36:43.400 --> 36:53.560
He wanted to be alone and think. In 1987 he went to the Kalahari Desert in Botswana with his friend

36:53.560 --> 36:59.640
the writer Laurent Van de Poste. Then he went to a lonely island in Scotland.

37:00.840 --> 37:05.720
People did not like this. Why isn't Charles with Diana? They asked.

37:06.600 --> 37:14.040
In September the newspapers showed photos of Charles at Balmoral. But Diana was not with him.

37:15.160 --> 37:17.480
She was in London with William and Harry.

37:18.760 --> 37:25.000
Charles and Diana are not speaking said the newspapers. People began to ask questions about

37:25.000 --> 37:32.200
the royal marriage. Were Charles and Diana not happy? Diana did more charity work.

37:33.160 --> 37:38.360
She did a lot of work for the old people's charity, helped the aged and for people with

37:38.360 --> 37:46.440
AIDS acquired immune deficiency syndrome. She worked hard and children and old people loved her.

37:47.720 --> 37:53.400
Diana was not afraid of people with AIDS. One time she shook hands with an AIDS patient.

37:54.440 --> 38:00.120
The next day there were photographs in all the newspapers. They called her caring die.

38:02.200 --> 38:06.360
Two years later she visited the Harlem Hospital Centre in New York.

38:07.560 --> 38:11.080
The photographers took a picture of Diana and a child with AIDS.

38:12.280 --> 38:18.200
After that many people heard about the Harlem Hospital. They became interested in the children

38:18.200 --> 38:22.760
with AIDS there. So Diana's visit was a very good thing for the hospital.

38:24.280 --> 38:30.520
Now people were not just interested in Diana's clothes or hair. They were interested in her work

38:30.520 --> 38:36.440
as well.

38:43.640 --> 38:47.320
Chapter 6 Unhappy Times

38:48.920 --> 38:54.280
In January 1988 Charles and Diana went on another visit to Australia.

38:55.160 --> 38:59.000
Again everyone wanted to see Diana not Charles.

38:59.800 --> 39:05.000
Diana sang Australia's national song but Charles did not know the words.

39:06.120 --> 39:14.600
We love die shouted the people. Charles felt jealous of his wife. It was a difficult time for their marriage.

39:16.920 --> 39:22.040
Diana's mother Frances Shand Kidd knew about Diana's problems in her marriage.

39:23.000 --> 39:31.480
She tried to help her daughter. But in the summer of 1988 Frances's husband Peter Shand Kidd left her.

39:32.440 --> 39:38.040
Frances was very sad. Diana invited her mother to Kensington Palace in London.

39:38.920 --> 39:43.400
But Frances did not come. She did not want to leave her home in Scotland.

39:43.400 --> 39:49.640
In November 1988 Charles and Diana went to Paris.

39:50.920 --> 39:57.560
This visit was very successful. Diana looked beautiful and Charles made speeches in French.

39:59.080 --> 40:06.120
Then on the 14th of November 1988 there was a big dance at Buckingham Palace for Charles's 40th

40:06.120 --> 40:16.520
birthday. In the autumn of 1989 James Hewitt went to work in Germany. Diana did not want him to go.

40:18.280 --> 40:26.600
At this time she met a new male friend James Gilby. Gilby's job was selling expensive cars.

40:28.280 --> 40:31.240
Diana and James Gilby began to meet in London.

40:32.200 --> 40:41.400
On New Year's Eve, the 31st of December 1989, someone recorded Diana and James Gilby talking on the telephone.

40:41.400 --> 40:47.480
Gilby said, I love you. Diana did not know about the recording.

40:48.920 --> 40:56.840
Fergie and Prince Andrew also had problems in their marriage. Andrew was often away for a long time with his job in the Navy.

40:57.800 --> 41:04.680
Fergie went to Australia for six weeks. There she met a handsome American, Steve Wyatt.

41:06.760 --> 41:11.000
James Hewitt returned to England and then went with the army to Iraq.

41:12.520 --> 41:19.160
While he was in Iraq, Diana telephoned him. She sent him letters and expensive food.

41:20.040 --> 41:26.120
In 1991, some newspaper reporters started writing about Diana and James Hewitt.

41:27.320 --> 41:31.000
Diana did not want people to find out about her relationship with Hewitt.

41:31.880 --> 41:34.760
When Hewitt came back from Iraq, she did not see him.

41:36.600 --> 41:39.720
Diana was very sad and felt very alone.

41:40.920 --> 41:42.760
What can I do? She thought.

41:42.760 --> 41:50.200
She decided to tell the public about her life. She wanted people to know her story.

41:51.160 --> 41:57.000
But she could not do this alone. So she asked a reporter, Andrew Morton, to help her.

41:57.800 --> 42:03.240
She asked him to write a book about her life. She wanted him to talk to her friends.

42:04.200 --> 42:08.920
But she did not tell anyone in the royal family about the book. It was a secret.

42:08.920 --> 42:14.920
Many newspaper reporters liked Diana and felt sorry for her.

42:16.440 --> 42:22.600
Sometimes Diana took William and Harry to amusement parks, large parks which have rides

42:22.600 --> 42:28.520
and many different fun activities. She also took them on a skiing holiday to Austria.

42:29.400 --> 42:31.080
But Charles did not go with them.

42:32.040 --> 42:40.280
Where is Charles? Ask the newspapers. Diana is a loving mother, but Charles is a bad father.

42:42.440 --> 42:49.240
In June 1991, William had an accident at his school. A golf ball hit him on the head.

42:50.600 --> 42:55.400
Charles and Diana took William to the Great Ormond Street Hospital for sick children in London.

42:56.520 --> 42:58.040
William needed an operation.

42:58.120 --> 43:04.040
Diana stayed with William at the hospital all night. But Charles left.

43:05.000 --> 43:08.920
What kind of father are you? Ask the newspapers the next day.

43:10.840 --> 43:15.400
On the 1st of July 1991, Diana was 30 years old.

43:16.600 --> 43:23.640
The 29th of July was Charles and Diana's 10th wedding anniversary. But their marriage was not a happy one.

